<HEAD>Two Children Dead In Separate Accidental Shootings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIRAMAR, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 10-year-old boy dialed 911 and frantically
pleaded with operators to save his little sister, an 8-year-old girl
he shot with the pistol he found in his father's dresser drawer.
   ``I shot her. I didn't mean to,'' Sean Smith pleaded as his
sister Erin was dying. ``Please don't die. Please God, please, don't
be dead.''
   The 911 operator kept him talking until police showed up. But the
girl, a second-grader, died within minutes of the shooting Monday.
   Erin's parents have arranged a private memorial service Friday at
Miramar United Methodist Church. Her ashes will be spread at a
Central Florida campground where the family spent Memorial Day
weekend.
   In Orlando, a teen-ager playing with a .357-caliber Magnum
handgun taken from his father's briefcase accidentally shot a
10-year-old friend in the head. Fourth-grader Scott Feltner died at
Orlando Regional Medical Center on Tuesday.
   No charges were filed in either case.
