<HEAD>Landslide Throws Crowded Bus off Hill Road</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAMMU, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At least 50 people were killed when a
landslide hurled the crowded bus they were riding in into a ravine
in the northern state of Jammu-Kashmir, officials and news reports
said.
   The bodies of ten passengers were recovered from site of
Wednesday's accident near Srinagar and at least 20 people were
hospitalized with injuries, said M.S. Pandit, the top civilian
administrator for the Srinigar region.
   The United News of India news agency quoted an unnamed government
spokesman as saying 50 people were killed.
   Pandit said the bus was traveling from the western town of Uri to
Srinagar on a remote hill road when was caught under the landslide.
The vehicle toppled hundreds of feet into a ravine, he said.
