<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--MusicalMayhem     06-08 0156</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Musical Mayhem,0158</SECOND>
<HEAD>^Wife's Organ Music Ends in Divorce, Arson</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EXETER, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 59-year-old man who said he was driven
mad by his wife's constant playing on an electric organ was
convicted of arson for setting their house on fire.
   ``If you have someone playing the organ 24 hours a day, seven
days a week, how would you react? She didn't play it very well,
either,'' George Bangs said after he was sentenced in Exeter Crown
Court on Wednesday to two years on probation.
   Bangs said his wife's organ playing had destroyed their marriage,
and he set fire to their home of 22 years when faced with the
prospect of selling it to pay for a divorce. His wife's car also was
damaged.
   The episode hasn't stopped his now-divorced wife's musical
endeavors, Bangs said.
   ``She still plays the organ, and so does the man she lives with.
They play duets together,'' he said.
</TEXT>
