<HEAD>60 Reported Drowned When Ship Capsizes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAPUTO, Mozambique (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger boat capsized and sank as
it was preparing to leave a dock, drowning 60 people and leaving at
least 30 survivors, official radio reported Thursday.
   Radio Mozambique said the accident occurred Wednesday at
Inhambane Bay on the southern coast.
   The report, monitored by the national news agency, AIM, said the
boat, named The Mozambique, was preparing to leave port at Inhambane
City to cross the bay to Maxixe.
   The radio said it was not known how many passengers the boat was
carrying, but 30 vessels were searching for more survivors. The
report said the cause of the accident was not known.
   Local authorities declared two days of morning in Inhambane
proivince, AIM reported.
   Early this year, 40 people died when a ship sank in the bay, a
narrow inlet that penetrates about 25 miles into the coastline on
the Indian Ocean.
