<HEAD>President Says First Lady OK</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Bush</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush told a televised news conference
that first lady Barbara Bush, who turned 64 Thursday, was ``doing
just fine'' in keeping a thyroid problem under control.
   Bush added the personal note when a reporter said he wanted to
relay a happy birthday wish to Mrs. Bush.
   The president joked that the first lady did not particularly want
the birthday celebrated. Then he added that she appreciated the
messages of concern that had flooded into the White House over her
condition.
