<HEAD>Bush: Human Rights Concerns Extend to South Africa</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush said Thursday his concerns about
human rights in China extend to all countries, including South
Africa.
   Bush was asked at a news conference whether his concerns about
the Chinese suppression of the pro-democracy student movement
extended to other areas, including South Africa and the
Israeli-occupied West Bank.
   ``It certainly does,'' he said. ``The concern is universal. ...
We have to speak out in favor of human rights. We are not going to
remake the world, but we should stand for something.''
   As for South Africa, he said, ``Absolutely. Appalling apartheid
must end.''
   He made no specific reference to the West Bank.
