<HEAD>Father, Daughter Die on Same Day in Separate Accidents</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOUNT PLEASANT, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man and his 16-year-old daughter
were killed 11{ hours apart Thursday in separate accidents involving
pickup trucks in which they were passengers, state police said.
   The truck carrying Ronald Lee Pirl Sr. of Normalville apparently
was traveling fast when it went out of control at a curve on state
Route 1003 at 1:15 p.m., said Trooper David Heckman.
   The vehicle overturned twice, ejecting Pirl, 38, then killing him
as it landed on him, police said.
   The driver of the truck, Ronda Carbaugh, 25, of Normalville and
her 4-year-old daughter Shannon were in serious condition at
Pittsburgh's Allegheny General Hospital, said nursing supervisor
Marcie Zebley.
   Earlier, at 1:45 a.m., Pirl's daughter, Barbara, was killed when
the pickup truck she was riding in overturned and skidded into a
utility pole along Pennsylvania Route 31. Also killed was Sheila
Moore, 17, of Connellsville.
   The driver of the truck, Thomas Vanorsdale, 20, of Canfield,
Ohio, was in fair condition at Frick Community Hospital in Mount
Pleasant. Another passenger was in critical condition.
