<FIRST>r i AM-Panama-Endara     06-08 0156</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Panama-Endara,0161</SECOND>
<HEAD>Shouts of Support at Funeral for Endara's Wife</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Funeral services were held Thursday
for Marcela Cambra de Endara, wife of opposition presidential
nominee Guillermo Endara, to shouts of ``Justice!'' and ``Endara,
friend, the people are with you!''
   Mrs. Cambra, 48, died Tuesday of a heart attack.
   More than 1,000 mourners applauded when the Rev. Javier Francisco
Villanueva, who officiated, praised Endara and referred to him as
``president-elect.''
   Endara, 53, and his supporters say he won the May 7 election.
International observers said Gen. Manuel Antonio Noriega, Panama's
de facto leader, rigged the balloting in favor of his candidate,
then annulled the election when the fraud became obvious.
   ``Adios, first lady of the republic,'' read a large sign near the
cemetery.
   Anel Beliz, a spokesman for Endara, said President Bush
telephoned Endara to express condolences.
   The governments of West Germany, Spain, Brazil and Venezuela were
among those sending condolences.
</TEXT>
