   OPEC ministers struck a deal to restrain
production in order to keep bolstering oil prices, but crude futures
tumbled in U.S. trading on indications that some nations would
continue cheating.
   The accord signed Wednesday lifts OPEC's official production
ceiling to 19.5 million barrels a day for the July-December period
from 18.5 million barrels in effect for January-June.
   It was signed by all 13 members of the Organization of Petroleum
Exporting Countries.
