<FIRST>r f BC-AutoProduction     06-08 0147</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Auto Production,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>Production Up This Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
231,232 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
194,049, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago, in
which 255,189 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal
said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 140,945 cars this week,
compared with 121,995 a week ago and 170,279 in the same 1988 week.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 90,287,
compared with last week's 72,054 and last year's 84,910.
   Canadian automakers were to build 19,780 cars this week, down
from 22,962 a week ago and 27,198 a year ago.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 19,077, compared
with 19,610 a week ago and 20,461 in the same week last year.
</TEXT>
