<FIRST>r f BC-CarlsonHotels     06-08 0167</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Carlson Hotels,0174</SECOND>
<HEAD>Carlson Expansion Includes New Resort Chain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Carlson Companies Inc. said it plans a
350-hotel expansion including a new chain of franchised resorts.
   The Minnetonka-based group of hotel and restaurant companies,
which already controls 200 hotels, said it expects to control 550
locations with 103,500 rooms by 1992.
   The new resort chain, called Colony International Resorts, will
be operated by the group's 30-hotel Colony Hotels &amp; Resorts
division, which expects to add 100 new franchise and management
contracts by 1992, the company said Wednesday.
   Colony also will move its 20-worker Los Angeles headquarters to
Minnetonka and add 1,000 new jobs in the next two years under the
plan.
   Carlson Companies is a private company with about $5.3 billion in
annual revenue.
   In addition to the 100 Colony division hotels, 250 hotels will be
added during the expansion through other Carlson group chains,
including Radisson Hotels International and Country Hospitality Inns.
   The group also owns TGI Friday's restaurants and Country Kitchen
restaurants.
</TEXT>
